		 Remembering Ustad Bismillah Khan																																	Yaad-e-Bismillah is a tribute to the late legend Ustad Bismillah Khan, who gave the shehnai its glory. The programme is organised by the Ustads foster daughter and well-known vocalist of the Benaras gharana, Dr Soma Ghosh. The evening presents a 40-minute docudrama on Khansahab, depicting the guru-shishya parampara between the Ustad and his guru Ali Baux, and tracing the dramatic journey of his life, beginning with the divine learning of the shehnai and the colourful facets of his personality to his glorious end. The show has the likes of Pandit Jasraj, Girija Devi and Ustad Dilshad Khan, among others, paying tribute to the maestro. After the film show , Dr Soma Ghosh, along with the sons of Ustad Bismillah Khan, will render some of his favourite kajaris. A rare exhibition of the Khansahabs mood photographs will follow this performance. Finally, there will be a concert held by the exponents of the endangered classical instruments of India a subject of grave concern.					
